The article highlights the importance of the World Health Organization (WHO) and President Biden's decision to re-engage with the organization. However, it also emphasizes the need for holding the WHO to high standards and protecting its credibility. The article expresses concerns about the communication and process used in the early findings of the COVID-19 investigation. It calls for an independent report with expert findings free from intervention by the Chinese government. Additionally, it emphasizes the importance of China making its data from the early days of the outbreak available to better understand and prepare for future pandemics. The article concludes by advocating for transparent and robust processes for preventing and responding to health emergencies globally.